FOR HER INHERITANCE.

12:20.587 --> 12:23.790
NINE DID THIS.

12:23.790 --> 12:28.261
YOU BETTER SHUT THAT
LITTLE WHORE DOWN FOR GOOD, JIM.

12:28.261 --> 12:30.063
OR I WILL.

12:30.063 --> 12:34.034
DO YOU HEAR ME?
I WILL!

12:34.034 --> 12:36.937
I'M SORRY,
DID YOU SAY SOMETHING?

12:48.949 --> 12:51.552
[ SIREN WAILING ]

12:51.552 --> 12:55.288
[ Woman on P. A.]
<i>DR. FOREST, DIAL 102, PLEASE.</i>

12:55.288 --> 12:58.458
<i>DR. FOREST, PLEASE DIAL 102.</i>

12:58.458 --> 13:02.302
[ CRYING ]
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

13:04.437 --> 13:08.509
<i>DR. FOREST, PLEASE DIAL 102.</i>

13:08.509 --> 13:11.044
EXCUSE ME.

13:11.044 --> 13:13.346
EXCUSE ME!
YES?

13:13.346 --> 13:15.415
I'M JUST TRYING TO CHECK
ON MY SON.

13:15.415 --> 13:17.050
LADY,
THERE'S A LOT OF PEOPLE

13:17.050 --> 13:19.720
TRYING TO CHECK ON PATIENTS
AROUND HERE. LOOK AROUND.

13:19.720 --> 13:21.087
IS THE DOCTOR HERE?

13:21.087 --> 13:23.256
YES.
CAN I TALK TO HIM?

13:23.256 --> 13:25.892
SO YOU WANT ME TO PULL
HIM OUT OF SURGERY TO
COME AND TALK TO YOU?

13:25.892 --> 13:27.694
THERE ARE TWO DOCTORS ON CALL
TONIGHT.

13:27.694 --> 13:29.462
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

13:29.462 --> 13:32.666
NO.
I'LL WAIT.

13:32.666 --> 13:33.667
THANK YOU.

13:33.667 --> 13:35.969
DO YOU KNOW
HOW LONG HE'LL BE?

13:35.969 --> 13:37.838
WHEN YOU HEAR
THE PATIENT'S NAME CALLED,

13:37.838 --> 13:39.272
COME AND SPEAK
TO THE DOCTOR.

13:39.272 --> 13:40.607
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME...

13:40.607 --> 13:43.009
OOH.

13:43.009 --> 13:45.278
I HATE COUNTY HOSPITALS.

13:45.278 --> 13:48.949
DAMN, THESE PEOPLE WORK
ON MY NERVES.

13:48.949 --> 13:51.585
GO OUT ON A DAMN FRIDAY NIGHT,
SHOOT AND STAB EACH OTHER,

13:51.585 --> 13:54.354
THEN WE FIX THEM UP FOR THEM
TO DO IT AGAIN NEXT WEEKEND.

13:54.354 --> 13:57.524
MM‐HMM.
IT'S SO DAMN IGNORANT.

13:57.524 --> 14:01.334
YOU NEED TO TAKE
A BREAK...NOW.

14:01.334 --> 14:03.770
YES. I DO.

14:03.770 --> 14:05.405
I NEED A CIGARETTE.

14:05.405 --> 14:07.508
GO TAKE IT.
THANK YOU.

14:07.508 --> 14:10.611
UH, EXCUSE ME.
WHAT WAS YOUR SON'S NAME?

14:10.611 --> 14:12.212
BENNY.
BENJAMIN YOUNG.

14:12.212 --> 14:14.247
BENJAMIN YOUNG.
UM...

14:14.247 --> 14:16.482
HE CAME IN
A FEW HOURS AGO.

14:16.482 --> 14:18.552
HE WAS SHOT?
NO, NO, NO.

14:18.552 --> 14:21.421
A CAR ACCIDENT.
CAR ACCIDENT. CAR ACCIDENT.

14:21.421 --> 14:23.489
BENJAMIN YOUNG.
I SEE HIM HERE.

14:23.489 --> 14:25.692
UM...THERE'S
NO UPDATES YET, SO...

14:25.692 --> 14:27.728
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

14:27.728 --> 14:29.129
THAT MEANS
HE'S PROBABLY IN SURGERY.

14:29.129 --> 14:30.731
THE DOCTOR UPDATES
AS HE CAN.

14:30.731 --> 14:31.598
SO WHEN WE KNOW, YOU KNOW.

14:31.598 --> 14:34.635
SO, I JUST HAVE TO WAIT.

14:34.635 --> 14:37.738
I'M SORRY, MISS ‐‐
HANNA.

14:37.738 --> 14:38.739
HANNA.

14:38.739 --> 14:41.575
LOOK, IT'S...[SCOFFS]
IT'S CRAZY.

14:41.575 --> 14:43.910
FRIDAY NIGHTS, FULL MOONS.

14:43.910 --> 14:46.780
WE SEE IT ALL
DOWN HERE, SO...

14:46.780 --> 14:48.515
WATCH THE DOOR.
WATCH THE DOOR.

14:48.515 --> 14:50.016
I WILL CHECK ON HIM, OKAY?

14:50.016 --> 14:51.652
THANK YOU.
I'LL GO CHECK.

14:51.652 --> 14:53.353
WHAT HAPPENED?

14:53.353 --> 14:55.455
6 YEARS OLD, HIT BY A DRIVER
UNDER THE INFLUENCE.

14:55.455 --> 14:56.523
THOSE ARE THE PARENTS.

14:56.523 --> 14:57.791
THEY DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THE CHILD WAS MISSING.

14:57.791 --> 14:59.092
OKAY.
YOU HAVE TO STAY THERE.

14:59.092 --> 15:00.326
DID YOU CALL THE POLICE?

15:00.326 --> 15:02.703
[ Crying ] YES, I CALLED.
WHERE ARE THEY?!

15:02.703 --> 15:04.705
THEY DON'T COME
AROUND HERE.

15:04.705 --> 15:06.306
DAMN IT!

15:06.306 --> 15:08.341
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU,
GIRL?

15:08.341 --> 15:10.210
IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

15:10.210 --> 15:12.078
NOTHING'S EVER YOUR FAULT,
IS IT?

15:12.078 --> 15:13.647
EVER YOUR DAMN FAULT.

15:13.647 --> 15:14.948
IT IS YOUR FAULT!

15:14.948 --> 15:17.283
BUT I ‐‐ BUT I ‐‐
IF I DON'T ‐‐

15:17.283 --> 15:19.352
OUT OF MY FACE.
I'M SORRY.

15:19.352 --> 15:22.222
I TOLD THAT JUDGE
NOT TO GIVE YOU VISITATION.

15:22.222 --> 15:25.526
I TOLD THE JUDGE!
NOW LOOK.

15:25.526 --> 15:28.094
NOW LOOK!

15:32.032 --> 15:34.601
[ SIGHS ]

15:34.601 --> 15:36.937
WHAT A TRYING DAY.

15:36.937 --> 15:38.739
David: HONEY?

15:38.739 --> 15:40.106
YES?

15:40.106 --> 15:42.509
ALL THROUGH DINNER,
NOT A WORD?

15:42.509 --> 15:43.744
ABOUT?

15:43.744 --> 15:45.011
JEFFREY.
[ SIGHS ]

15:45.011 --> 15:47.247
I DON'T WANT TO TALK
ABOUT THIS PHASE.

15:47.247 --> 15:49.349
IT'LL PASS.
LIKE THE TERRIBLE TWOS.

15:49.349 --> 15:51.918
TERRIBLE TWOS?
YES.

15:51.918 --> 15:54.254
REMEMBER WHEN JEFFREY USED TO
PULL EVERYTHING DOWN

15:54.254 --> 15:56.422
OFF THE TABLE,
BROKE MY GRANDMOTHER'S VASE?

15:56.422 --> 15:57.423
VERONICA.

15:57.423 --> 15:59.826
I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT,
DAVID.

15:59.826 --> 16:02.736
YOU ARE WRONG.
TERRIBLY WRONG.

16:02.736 --> 16:05.171
AND YET YOU STILL BRING UP
THIS SUBJECT.

16:05.171 --> 16:08.108
YOU ARE NOT GONNA TELL ME
THAT YOU DON'T LOVE OUR SON

16:08.108 --> 16:09.109
JUST BECAUSE ‐‐

16:09.109 --> 16:10.711
DON'T YOU DARE SAY IT.

16:10.711 --> 16:14.414
JEFFREY IS GAY,
VERONICA.

16:14.414 --> 16:16.416
YOU NEED TO FACE IT.

16:16.416 --> 16:19.720
NO, HE NEEDS TO FACE THE FACT
THAT HE'S NOT.

16:19.720 --> 16:23.957
SOMETIMES YOU ARE SO CONFUSING
TO ME.

16:23.957 --> 16:27.227
I'VE SEEN YOU BE SO OPEN‐MINDED
ON SO MANY OTHER ISSUES.

16:27.227 --> 16:29.796
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
I AM OPEN‐MINDED.

16:29.796 --> 16:30.997
ARE YOU?
YES!

16:30.997 --> 16:32.699
I DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH GAY PEOPLE.

16:32.699 --> 16:34.467
[ SCOFFS ]
SURELY YOU MUST.

16:34.467 --> 16:37.704
I HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH MY ONLY SON BEING...

16:40.240 --> 16:43.143
I CAN'T BEAR THE THOUGHT
OF THAT.

16:43.143 --> 16:47.881
YOU SAID SOME TERRIBLY HURTFUL
THINGS TO HIM.

16:47.881 --> 16:49.750
WELL, WE'RE EVEN.

16:49.750 --> 16:53.053
VERONICA,
I'M DISAPPOINTED IN YOU.

16:53.053 --> 16:56.156
GREATLY DISAPPOINTED.

16:56.156 --> 17:01.668
WELL...NEVER THOUGHT
I'D HEAR YOU SAY THOSE WORDS.

17:01.668 --> 17:05.238
WELL, HONEY, AT THIS POINT,
IT REALLY DOESN'T MATTER.

17:05.238 --> 17:08.008
WHAT IF SOMETHING WERE TO HAPPEN
TO HIM?

17:08.008 --> 17:09.876
SOMETHING CERTAINLY WILL HAPPEN
TO HIM

17:09.876 --> 17:11.477
IF HE CONTINUES
DOWN THIS ROAD.

17:11.477 --> 17:13.547
MEANING?

17:13.547 --> 17:15.481
HEARTBREAK, DAVID.

17:15.481 --> 17:17.884
EVERY DAY.

17:17.884 --> 17:19.953
IT'S BAD ENOUGH
HE'S GOT TO FIGHT THE FIGHT

17:19.953 --> 17:21.655
OF BEING A BLACK MAN
IN THIS WORLD

17:21.655 --> 17:24.725
AND NOW HE'S GOT TO ADD...THAT
TO IT.

17:24.725 --> 17:26.492
I WON'T HAVE IT.

17:29.495 --> 17:32.966
YOU KNOW HOW MANY CHILDREN
COMMIT SUICIDE

17:32.966 --> 17:35.836
BECAUSE THEY WOULD RATHER BE
DEAD THAN COME OUT

17:35.836 --> 17:37.671
AND FACE THE CRUELTY
OF THIS WORLD?

17:37.671 --> 17:39.840
I AM NOT TALKING
ABOUT THIS WORLD.

17:39.840 --> 17:41.307
I'M TALKING ABOUT MY SON.

17:41.307 --> 17:43.977
YES.
AND JEFFREY WOULD NOT DO THAT.

17:43.977 --> 17:47.147
HE'S TOO STRONG FOR THAT.

17:47.147 --> 17:50.216
EXACTLY.
HE IS.

17:50.216 --> 17:53.053
HE CAME OUT.

17:53.053 --> 17:56.356
SO ALLOW JEFFREY TO BE WHO HE IS
IN HIS OWN STRENGTH.

17:56.356 --> 17:58.525
WE ARE NOT THE KIND OF PARENTS
THAT WILL ALLOW THAT.

17:58.525 --> 18:00.527
YOU ARE NOT THE KIND OF MOTHER
WHO WOULD ALLOW THAT.

18:00.527 --> 18:02.035
AND WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

18:02.035 --> 18:05.105
I'M GOING TO STAND BY
MY SON.

18:05.105 --> 18:08.809
DAVID, DON'T ENCOURAGE
THIS FOOLISHNESS.

18:08.809 --> 18:11.945
I'M NOT ENCOURAGING
ANYTHING.

18:11.945 --> 18:14.314
I AM ALLOWING HIM TO BE.

18:14.314 --> 18:18.652
I LOVE MY SON,
AND I'M GOING TO STAND BY HIM.

18:18.652 --> 18:21.187
SO, YOU'RE
TURNING AGAINST ME, TOO.

18:21.187 --> 18:23.323
NO, I AM NOT
TURNING AGAINST YOU.

18:23.323 --> 18:24.858
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

18:24.858 --> 18:27.193
NOR WILL I TURN AGAINST
OUR SON.

18:34.635 --> 18:36.436
[ SIGHS ]

18:36.436 --> 18:38.304
ALL RIGHT, HONEY.

18:42.676 --> 18:45.812
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

18:52.553 --> 18:54.020
Amanda: DID YOU SEE THE LOOK
ON MY MOM'S FACE?

18:54.020 --> 18:55.121
Candace:
UH‐HUH. AND YOUR DAD'S.

18:55.121 --> 18:57.090
YEAH.
I LOVED IT.

18:57.090 --> 18:59.459
GOOD.
I FEEL SO GREAT.

18:59.459 --> 19:01.968
WOW.

19:01.968 --> 19:03.870
I DIDN'T KNOW THIS WOULD FEEL
THIS GOOD.

19:03.870 --> 19:06.573
HMM.

19:10.711 --> 19:12.946
IT'S NICE
TO FEEL GOOD, HUH?

19:12.946 --> 19:15.381
YEAH.

19:15.381 --> 19:18.084
IS THAT JEFFREY?

19:18.084 --> 19:20.386
JEFFREY?

19:20.386 --> 19:22.956
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:22.956 --> 19:25.792
ARE YOU OKAY?

19:27.994 --> 19:30.764
HE'S OKAY.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:30.764 --> 19:34.134
AMANDA, CAN YOU GO MAKE US
SOME TEA, PLEASE?

19:34.134 --> 19:36.336
YEAH, SURE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

19:36.336 --> 19:39.139
NO RUSH.
WE'LL BE UP IN A SECOND.

19:39.139 --> 19:41.174
OKAY.
YEAH.

19:45.746 --> 19:48.114
LET ME GUESS.
[ SIGHS ]

19:48.114 --> 19:50.584
YOUR MOTHER FOUND OUT?

19:50.584 --> 19:52.886
[ SNIFFLES ]

19:55.756 --> 19:57.357
YEAH.

19:59.560 --> 20:01.602
HOW DID SHE FIND OUT?

20:01.602 --> 20:04.638
I TOLD HER.

20:04.638 --> 20:07.173
TOLD HER WHAT?

20:11.512 --> 20:13.413
THAT I'M GAY.

20:17.684 --> 20:20.286
GLAD YOU CAN ADMIT IT.

20:20.286 --> 20:21.955
WASN'T THAT BAD, WAS IT?

20:21.955 --> 20:25.659
SCARY.

20:25.659 --> 20:28.128
WHY?

20:28.128 --> 20:31.097
JUDGMENT.

20:33.667 --> 20:39.172
WHOEVER DOESN'T GET IT
DOESN'T MATTER.

20:39.172 --> 20:41.842
DOESN'T' WORK THAT WAY
AROUND HERE, CANDACE.

20:41.842 --> 20:43.877
THEN CHANGE IT.

20:43.877 --> 20:46.913
[ SIGHS ]

20:46.913 --> 20:50.884
IT'S NOT SO SIMPLE.

20:50.884 --> 20:53.419
WHAT DID YOUR MOTHER SAY?

20:53.419 --> 20:56.823
SHE WAS SO COLD.

20:56.823 --> 20:59.893
JUST COLD.

21:02.035 --> 21:03.203
SHE...

21:03.203 --> 21:06.239
SHE LOOKED AT ME
LIKE I WAS SCUM.

21:06.239 --> 21:09.142
LIKE I HAD TAKEN
EVERY ONE OF HER DREAMS

21:09.142 --> 21:10.711
AND TRAMPLED ON THEM.

21:13.714 --> 21:17.317
YOUR DREAMS
ARE NOT HER DREAMS.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.520
JEFFREY,
THIS IS YOUR LIFE.

21:19.520 --> 21:21.788
YOU HAVE TO LIVE IT
FOR YOU.

21:21.788 --> 21:24.124
AND WHAT CAN SHE DO TO YOU
ANYWAY?

21:24.124 --> 21:27.027
SHE CANCELED
MY CREDIT CARDS.

21:27.027 --> 21:31.097
SHE KICKED ME OUT
OF MY APARTMENT, THE FACILITY.

21:31.097 --> 21:35.201
SHE...CLOSED
MY BANK ACCOUNTS,

21:35.201 --> 21:38.605
FIRED ME,
GOD KNOWS WHAT ELSE.

21:38.605 --> 21:40.941
YEAH.

21:40.941 --> 21:43.910
[ SNIFFLES ]
YEAH.

21:43.910 --> 21:47.914
SHE'S SERIOUS ABOUT HER CONTROL
OVER YOU.

21:47.914 --> 21:49.816
[ SNIFFLES ]

21:49.816 --> 21:52.052
[ SIGHS ]

21:54.855 --> 21:57.591
I DON'T HAVE ANYWHERE
TO GO.

21:57.591 --> 22:00.260
YES, YOU DO.

22:00.260 --> 22:02.769
YOU COULD STAY HERE WITH US.
COME ON.

22:02.769 --> 22:05.071
NO.
NO, I‐I‐I CAN'T.

22:05.071 --> 22:08.675
I‐I CAN'T DO THAT.
UH, SURE YOU CAN.

22:08.675 --> 22:11.812
UNTIL WE FIGURE THIS
ALL OUT.

22:11.812 --> 22:13.514
LET'S GO.

22:13.514 --> 22:17.083
WHY ARE YOU BEING SO NICE
TO ME?

22:17.083 --> 22:18.985
LOOK AT ME.

22:22.756 --> 22:26.292
BECAUSE YOU'RE FINALLY
BEING NICE TO YOURSELF.

22:32.833 --> 22:35.435
I DON'T KNOW
HOW I CAN REPAY YOU.

22:35.435 --> 22:38.539
YOU'RE CUTE.

22:38.539 --> 22:42.175
I COULD PIMP YOU OUT.

22:42.175 --> 22:45.478
SCARY PART IS
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

22:48.081 --> 22:49.783
I'M KIDDING.

22:49.783 --> 22:51.652
YEAH?
YOU'RE KIDDING.

22:51.652 --> 22:54.955
UM, A LITTLE BIT.

22:54.955 --> 22:56.690
LET'S GO.

23:00.801 --> 23:03.069
COME ON.

23:18.885 --> 23:22.055
[ Woman on P. A. ]
<i>DR. FOREST, DIAL 182 PLEASE.</i>

23:22.055 --> 23:24.958
<i>DR. FOREST, PLEASE DIAL 182.</i>

23:24.958 --> 23:27.160
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

23:27.160 --> 23:30.531
I BOUGHT A SODA
AND TWO FELL.

23:30.531 --> 23:32.666
WOULD YOU LIKE IT?

23:32.666 --> 23:34.434
NO, THANK YOU.

23:34.434 --> 23:36.770
C‐CAN I HAVE IT?

23:36.770 --> 23:38.071
YOU SURE CAN.

23:40.173 --> 23:42.375
DON'T CARE TO SAY
THANK YOU?

23:42.375 --> 23:45.111
THANK YOU.

23:45.111 --> 23:47.413
YOU'RE WELCOME.

23:47.413 --> 23:49.415
WHY AREN'T THESE DOCTORS
GETTING BACK TO ME?

23:49.415 --> 23:50.884
WHY AREN'T THEY TALKING
TO ME?

23:50.884 --> 23:53.386
YEAH, I KNOW.
[ SCOFFS ]

23:53.386 --> 23:55.255
I'VE BEEN WAITING, TOO.

23:55.255 --> 23:57.524
THESE COUNTY HOSPITALS.

23:57.524 --> 24:00.961
I WAS JUST SAYING
THE SAME THING.

24:00.961 --> 24:02.936
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIND OUT
SOMETHING ABOUT MY SON

24:02.936 --> 24:04.671
FOR TWO HOURS.

24:04.671 --> 24:06.472
WON'T NOBODY TELL ME
NOTHING.

24:06.472 --> 24:09.109
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

24:09.109 --> 24:12.779
[ Voice breaking ]
HE WAS IN A CAR WRECK.

24:12.779 --> 24:14.180
OH, I'M SORRY.

24:14.180 --> 24:16.082
THANK YOU.

24:16.082 --> 24:17.951
AND I'M SORRY
FOR Y'ALL, TOO.

24:20.887 --> 24:22.388
I'M PRAYING.

24:22.388 --> 24:25.992
WELL,
PRAY FOR MY GRANDDAUGHTER.

24:25.992 --> 24:28.929
YES, I WILL.

24:28.929 --> 24:34.000
I'M SORRY.
I'M JUST SO UPSET, BUT...

24:37.237 --> 24:39.873
...THAT'S MY HEART IN THERE.
MM‐HMM.

24:39.873 --> 24:41.908
YOU KNOW,
SHE IS SO SWEET.

24:41.908 --> 24:45.011
SO INNOCENT.

24:45.011 --> 24:46.813
SO PURE.

24:49.015 --> 24:52.052
I KNOW THE FEELING.

24:52.052 --> 24:56.456
I WAS RAISING MY GRANDBABY
FOR A FEW YEARS.

24:56.456 --> 24:59.092
TILL MY DAUGHTER TOOK HIM
FROM ME.

24:59.092 --> 25:01.602
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH THESE YOUNG KIDS TODAY?

25:01.602 --> 25:03.403
MM‐HMM.
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER.

25:03.403 --> 25:05.539
LOOK AT HER, TWITCHING.

25:05.539 --> 25:08.642
SHE WANT TO GET OUT OF HERE
SO BAD.

25:08.642 --> 25:10.143
SHE WANT TO GET HIGH.

25:10.143 --> 25:11.712
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO?

25:11.712 --> 25:14.314
I'M NOT LEAVING MY BABY.

25:16.382 --> 25:18.852
YOU KNOW YOU'RE COMING DOWN
ON THAT HIGH.

25:18.852 --> 25:20.721
AND YOU KNOW WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
WHEN YOU DO.

25:20.721 --> 25:23.256
I'M...FINE.

25:25.892 --> 25:28.995
HOW COULD YOU JUST LEAVE HER
UNATTENDED LIKE THAT?

25:28.995 --> 25:31.031
I ONLY LOOKED AWAY
FOR A SECOND!

25:31.031 --> 25:33.299
YOU'RE A LIAR.
YOU ARE.

25:33.299 --> 25:34.868
YOU WERE GETTING HIGH.

25:34.868 --> 25:37.037
I WASN'T!

25:38.539 --> 25:40.541
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:42.408 --> 25:45.746
<i>DR. KRAVITZ, YOU HAVE A VISITOR</i>
<i>IN THE MAIN LOBBY.</i>

25:45.746 --> 25:48.381
<i>DR. KRAVITZ, A VISITOR</i>
<i>IN THE MAIN LOBBY.</i>

25:50.884 --> 25:52.418
MICHAEL.

25:52.418 --> 25:54.254
OH, REVEREND.

25:54.254 --> 25:56.256
HOW ARE YOU?

25:56.256 --> 25:59.526
I'M NOT GOOD.
I'M NOT GOOD.

25:59.526 --> 26:00.827
HAVE THE POLICE
BEEN HERE YET?

26:00.827 --> 26:04.304
NO.
THAT'S WHY I CALLED YOU.

26:04.304 --> 26:06.339
YOU KNOW THEY DON'T CARE
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENS

26:06.339 --> 26:08.441
TO THE LITTLE BLACK KIDS
IN OUR NEIGHBORHOOD.

26:08.441 --> 26:10.611
WELL, I CALLED
THE CHIEF OF POLICE.

26:10.611 --> 26:13.079
HE'S SENDING SOMEONE
DOWN HERE.

26:13.079 --> 26:14.748
FINALLY.
[ SIGHS ]

26:14.748 --> 26:18.519
I TOLD THAT JUDGE
THEY SHOULDN'T GIVE HER CUSTODY.

26:18.519 --> 26:20.787
HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM THE DOCTORS YET?

26:20.787 --> 26:22.823
THEY WON'T TALK TO US.

26:22.823 --> 26:25.191
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS DOWN HERE
IN THESE PUBLIC HOSPITALS.

26:25.191 --> 26:26.426
I'LL TRY TO FIND
SOMETHING OUT.

26:26.426 --> 26:28.895
THANK YOU.
SURE.

26:28.895 --> 26:30.564
REVEREND, EXCUSE ME.

26:30.564 --> 26:31.898
THIS LADY RIGHT HERE,

26:31.898 --> 26:33.466
S‐SHE WANTS TO KNOW
ABOUT HER SON, TOO.

26:33.466 --> 26:36.136
YOU DO?
YES, I DO.

26:36.136 --> 26:38.972
HIS NAME
IS BENNY YOUNG.

26:38.972 --> 26:40.040
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

26:40.040 --> 26:43.644
HIT AND RUN.
AND LEFT IN THE STREETS.

26:43.644 --> 26:45.879
DOES HE DRIVE A TOW TRUCK?

26:45.879 --> 26:46.980
YES.

26:46.980 --> 26:48.549
YOU KNOW HIM?

26:48.549 --> 26:51.351
WAS HE ON MATTHEWS?

26:51.351 --> 26:53.119
THAT'S WHAT
THE POLICE SAID.

26:53.119 --> 26:54.387
MY GOD.

26:54.387 --> 26:58.291
THE SAME MAN THAT RAN OVER
YOUR GRANDDAUGHTER

26:58.291 --> 27:00.493
TURNED THE CORNER
AND HIT YOUR SON.

27:00.493 --> 27:02.803
NO, WHAT?!
I'M SORRY.

27:02.803 --> 27:04.505
HE JUST KEPT GOING?

27:04.505 --> 27:07.473
HIT THAT LITTLE GIRL
AND BENNY AND JUST KEPT ‐‐

27:07.473 --> 27:08.575
I SAW.

27:08.575 --> 27:10.577
SAW WHO, BABY? MY SON?

27:10.577 --> 27:12.913
THE MAN WHO DID IT.

27:12.913 --> 27:14.681
Both: WHAT?
YEAH.

27:14.681 --> 27:16.650
WHY THE HELL DIDN'T YOU
TELL ANYBODY?!

27:16.650 --> 27:19.185
MICHAEL.
WHERE?

27:19.185 --> 27:20.854
WHERE WAS HE?

27:20.854 --> 27:22.422
HE WAS AT THE PARTY.

27:22.422 --> 27:23.824
GETTING HIGH WITH YOU,
RIGHT?

27:23.824 --> 27:25.191
HE LEFT.

27:25.191 --> 27:26.660
WHAT WAS HE DRIVING?

27:26.660 --> 27:29.195
ALL BLACK, FOUR‐DOOR CAR.

27:29.195 --> 27:31.264
WHAT DID HE LOOK LIKE?

27:31.264 --> 27:34.467
UH, HE WAS A WHITE MAN.
HE HAD BLACK HAIR.

27:34.467 --> 27:38.138
HE HAD NICE CLOTHES ON,
NICE SHOES ON.

27:38.138 --> 27:40.406
I COULD TELL HE WAS FROM
ACROSS THE TRACKS.

27:40.406 --> 27:43.143
I COULD TELL FROM THE WAY
HE LOOKED WHEN HE WALKED IN.

27:43.143 --> 27:44.811
Michael:
DID YOU GET HIS NAME?

27:44.811 --> 27:46.780
NO.
THEY WAS GONNA ROB HIM.

27:46.780 --> 27:48.815
WHO?

27:48.815 --> 27:50.350
FRANKLIN AND BRUTE.

27:50.350 --> 27:53.854
TINA, THINK.
TELL US WHAT HAPPENED.

27:53.854 --> 27:57.357
HE ‐‐ HE ‐‐ HE FOUGHT THEM OFF,
HE GOT IN HIS CAR,

27:57.357 --> 28:00.026
BUT HE WAS GOING
THE WRONG WAY.

28:00.026 --> 28:02.969
[ Crying ] HE GOT TURNED AROUND
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD,

28:02.969 --> 28:07.073
CAME BACK DOWN THE STREET,
AND HE WAS FLYING.

28:07.073 --> 28:08.509
HE HIT LIZZIE.

28:08.509 --> 28:11.111
AND THEN HE WAS GONE.

28:11.111 --> 28:13.914
WHEN THE POLICE GET HERE,
I NEED YOU TO TALK TO THEM.

28:13.914 --> 28:16.049
WE GONNA TRY TO GET
A SKETCH ARTIST DOWN HERE,

28:16.049 --> 28:17.984
AND WE GONNA FIND OUT
WHO DID THIS.

28:17.984 --> 28:20.120
[ CRYING ]

28:39.105 --> 28:41.107
THERE ARE NO CALLS.

28:41.107 --> 28:44.010
I'M SORRY.
DID I WAKE YOU?

28:44.010 --> 28:45.912
NO.

28:45.912 --> 28:47.814
[ SIGHS ]

28:47.814 --> 28:49.550
MY BROTHER...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

28:49.550 --> 28:51.652
WE USUALLY SPEAK
TWICE A DAY,

28:51.652 --> 28:54.387
AND I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM HIM
ALL DAY.

28:54.387 --> 28:55.388
[ BEEPING ]

28:55.388 --> 28:57.457
IT'S CRAZY.

29:01.001 --> 29:03.403
I CAN'T SLEEP.

29:03.403 --> 29:05.906
DO YOU WANT A DRINK?

29:05.906 --> 29:08.074
NO.

29:08.074 --> 29:11.411
MAYBE THERE ARE
TOO MANY LIGHTS ON.

29:11.411 --> 29:15.749
[ SIGHS ]
YEAH.

29:15.749 --> 29:18.018
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

29:26.860 --> 29:29.763
YOU KNOW YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT WYATT.

29:29.763 --> 29:32.132
THAT HE'S STRAIGHT?

29:32.132 --> 29:34.467
I KNOW.

29:34.467 --> 29:37.771
WAS I ALSO RIGHT ABOUT
YOU BEING IN LOVE WITH HIM?

29:37.771 --> 29:41.341
CANDACE, JUST STOP.
JEFFREY, COME ON.

29:41.341 --> 29:43.910
WE'RE TALKING.
[ SIGHS ]

29:43.910 --> 29:46.112
YES.

29:46.112 --> 29:51.752
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR HEARTACHE
IN A SITUATION LIKE THAT.

29:51.752 --> 29:53.419
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

29:53.419 --> 29:54.988
I TOLD YOU.

29:54.988 --> 29:57.057
I LOVE THE KIDS.

29:57.057 --> 30:00.594
THAT'S NOT ALL.

30:00.594 --> 30:03.169
WHAT?
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE THERE.

30:03.169 --> 30:04.738
SOMETHING LIKE?

30:04.738 --> 30:05.739
COME ON.

30:05.739 --> 30:08.742
OBVIOUSLY YOU FORGET
I'M A PSYCHOLOGIST.

30:08.742 --> 30:11.845
AND YOU FORGET THAT
YOU DON'T HAVE A DEGREE YET.

30:11.845 --> 30:15.582
OKAY,
H‐HOW DO YOU EVEN...

30:15.582 --> 30:17.518
AMANDA, RIGHT.
MM‐HMM.

30:17.518 --> 30:20.086
WELL,
I WAS THREE CREDITS SHY.

30:20.086 --> 30:22.623
[ SIGHS ]

30:22.623 --> 30:25.592
WELL,
ALMOST DR. JEFFREY...

30:28.161 --> 30:30.063
...ANALYZE ME.

30:36.903 --> 30:39.039
OKAY.

30:41.708 --> 30:43.577
YOU'RE ALWAYS CALCULATING.

30:43.577 --> 30:46.279
ALL THE TIME.

30:46.279 --> 30:49.816
YOU SEEK STIMULUS,
CANDACE.

30:52.218 --> 30:54.955
LOTS OF CHILDHOOD TRAUMA.

30:54.955 --> 30:56.923
AND NOT THAT B. S.

30:56.923 --> 30:59.359
ABOUT YOUR PARENTS IN
THE WITNESS‐PROTECTION PROGRAM.

30:59.359 --> 31:04.805
YOU THRIVE ON DRAMA.

31:04.805 --> 31:08.208
YOU'RE ALWAYS ONE STEP AHEAD
OF EVERYBODY.

31:08.208 --> 31:11.211
SELLING YOUR BODY
ISN'T ABOUT MONEY.

31:11.211 --> 31:14.648
IT'S ABOUT POWER, CONTROL.

31:14.648 --> 31:17.584
YOU USE YOUR BODY
LIKE A WEAPON,

31:17.584 --> 31:21.622
TAKING OUT EVERY MAN
YOU THINK IS A TARGET.

31:21.622 --> 31:22.789
LIKE JUDGE CRYER.

31:22.789 --> 31:25.926
HMM.

31:25.926 --> 31:28.862
YEAH, OKAY. THERE'S NO NEED
TO ACKNOWLEDGE IT.

31:28.862 --> 31:30.997
I KNOW.

31:30.997 --> 31:34.835
I KNOW IT'S TRUE BY THE CONTROL
YOU'RE EXERCISING RIGHT NOW.

31:36.970 --> 31:40.373
I DON'T SEE EVERYTHING,

31:40.373 --> 31:43.276
BUT I DON'T MISS
ANYTHING.

31:43.276 --> 31:46.813
AND, CANDACE,
YOU HAVE A WEAKNESS.

31:46.813 --> 31:48.181
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS YET.

31:48.181 --> 31:51.151
MAYBE YOUR BROTHER,
BUT THEN AGAIN,

31:51.151 --> 31:53.453
YOU DON'T CARE ABOUT ANYBODY
UNLESS YOU LIKE THEM.

31:53.453 --> 31:55.321
THEN THEY'RE ALL TOYS
TO YOU

31:55.321 --> 31:57.824
UNTIL YOU GET TIRED OF PLAYING
WITH THEM.

31:57.824 --> 32:00.827
AND IF THEY MAKE YOU ANGRY,

32:00.827 --> 32:04.805
WHEW...YOU RUN OVER THEM
LIKE ROADKILL.

32:07.207 --> 32:09.475
HMM.

32:13.514 --> 32:15.415
I HAD A COUSIN.

32:15.415 --> 32:17.784
HIS NAME WAS STEVE.

32:17.784 --> 32:21.522
HE CALLED HIMSELF
LADY DIAMOND.

32:21.522 --> 32:26.426
HE WAS A TRANSVESTITE,
AND HE LOVED ME SO MUCH.

32:26.426 --> 32:29.863
HE WAS FIERCE.

32:29.863 --> 32:32.599
FROM THE TIME
I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,

32:32.599 --> 32:34.668
I WOULD SNEAK OUT WITH HIM.

32:37.437 --> 32:39.105
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:39.105 --> 32:41.307
AND FROM THE TIME
HE WAS A LITTLE KID,

32:41.307 --> 32:46.613
HE CAUGHT HELL IN THE HOOD
FOR BEING GAY AND FEMININE.

32:46.613 --> 32:49.583
AND I WANTED TO KICK
EVERYBODY'S ASS

32:49.583 --> 32:52.986
WHO HAD SOMETHING BAD TO SAY
ABOUT HIM.

32:52.986 --> 32:56.857
HE SHOWED ME THE ROPES,
BUT NOT THE GOOD ONES.

33:00.527 --> 33:04.771
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE WAS SO GOOD AT BEING BAD.

33:04.771 --> 33:07.240
I HAVE NOTHING ON HIM.

33:09.743 --> 33:13.346
HE TURNED TRICKS
FOOLING GUYS,

33:13.346 --> 33:17.450
ROBBING THEM,
CONNING THEM.

33:20.521 --> 33:23.423
WHEN WE WERE LITTLE,
HE WOULD F‐‐

33:23.423 --> 33:26.292
FLOOD THE BASEMENT
IN THE PROJECTS

33:26.292 --> 33:27.694
JUST TO GET RID OF THE RATS,

33:27.694 --> 33:30.831
AND WE WOULD BE SO EXCITED
WHEN HE WOULD DO IT.

33:30.831 --> 33:33.734
I WOULD WATCH ALL
THE NEIGHBORHOOD KIDS COME OVER

33:33.734 --> 33:38.371
AND BET ON WHICH RAT WOULD
MAKE IT OUT ALIVE.

33:38.371 --> 33:41.207
WHEN THE WATER WOULD RISE,
WE WOULD WATCH THESE RATS

33:41.207 --> 33:44.511
SWIM TO THIS BOARD THAT WAS
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE WATER.

33:44.511 --> 33:48.248
AND THEY WOULD START
TO KILL EACH OTHER

33:48.248 --> 33:50.416
WHEN IT GOT CROWDED.

33:50.416 --> 33:56.923
AND IT WAS THE SAME RAT
THAT ALWAYS MADE IT.

33:59.325 --> 34:02.268
AND MY COUSIN WOULD SAY,

34:02.268 --> 34:08.609
"THAT'S MY BAD BITCH RIGHT THERE
JUST LIKE CANDY CANE."

34:08.609 --> 34:12.345
HE CALLED ME CANDY CANE.

34:12.345 --> 34:19.319
HE SAID,
"CANDY CANE, YOU MY BAD BITCH.

34:21.321 --> 34:26.026
AND YOU'RE GONNA DO WHAT YOU
GOT TO DO TO GET OUT OF HERE."

34:26.026 --> 34:29.530
HE BELIEVED IN ME.

34:32.298 --> 34:34.434
I WISH YOU COULD HAVE MET HIM.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

34:34.434 --> 34:39.372
HE WOULD HAVE ‐‐ HE WOULD HAVE
READ YOU UP AND DOWN.

34:39.372 --> 34:41.374
OH, L‐LIKE YOU DID?

34:41.374 --> 34:43.376
NO, HONEY.
WORSE.

34:43.376 --> 34:46.279
[ SIGHS ]
SO, WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

34:46.279 --> 34:50.684
HE FOOLED THE WRONG GUY.

34:50.684 --> 34:54.621
THEY FOUND HIM HUNG
WITH HIS PENIS CUT OFF.

34:54.621 --> 34:57.658
DO YOU WORRY ABOUT THAT?

34:57.658 --> 35:00.493
I DON'T HAVE A PENIS.

35:00.493 --> 35:02.969
NO, NO, NO.
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

35:02.969 --> 35:06.807
[ CHUCKLES ]
JEFFREY.

35:06.807 --> 35:09.510
I FEAR NOTHING.

35:09.510 --> 35:12.212
HMM.

35:12.212 --> 35:14.848
THAT'S SCARY.

35:14.848 --> 35:16.683
WHY?

35:16.683 --> 35:21.021
IF YOU FEAR NOTHING,
THEN YOU LOVE NOTHING.

35:24.958 --> 35:27.327
YOU SHOULD GET SOME SLEEP.

35:28.394 --> 35:32.566
YOU HAVE A NEW LIFE TO START
TOMORROW.

35:32.566 --> 35:36.236
I'M ‐‐ UM, CANDACE.

35:36.236 --> 35:37.971
THANK YOU.

35:40.206 --> 35:43.043
I'M YOUR BAD BITCH?

35:43.043 --> 35:46.747
YOU'RE MY BAD BITCH.

35:46.747 --> 35:47.681
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:47.681 --> 35:50.984
GOOD NIGHT, JEFFREY.
GOOD NIGHT.

36:05.205 --> 36:07.708
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

36:13.413 --> 36:16.950
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT'D THEY SAY, REVEREND?

36:16.950 --> 36:19.285
YOUR SON'S STILL
IN SURGERY.

36:19.285 --> 36:21.722
IS HE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT?

36:21.722 --> 36:22.756
THEY DON'T KNOW YET.

36:24.190 --> 36:27.460
WHAT ABOUT MY GRANDBABY?
REVEREND, SAY SOMETHING.

36:27.460 --> 36:29.696
SHE DIED.
NO!

36:29.696 --> 36:31.097
WHAT?!

36:31.097 --> 36:32.566
I'M SO SORRY.

36:32.566 --> 36:35.168
NO!
DON'T TELL ME THAT.

36:35.168 --> 36:37.337
WE GONNA GET THIS GUY.

36:37.337 --> 36:40.006
AS THERE IS A GOD,
WE GONNA GET THIS GUY.

36:41.608 --> 36:44.144
SHE'S DEAD?

36:44.144 --> 36:45.579
YES.

36:45.579 --> 36:47.781
WE GOT TO GET HIM.
[ SNIFFLES ]

36:47.781 --> 36:51.084
WE GOT TO GET HIM.
WE WILL.

36:51.084 --> 36:53.086
TINA.

36:53.086 --> 36:56.222
TINA.

36:56.222 --> 36:59.292
Y‐YES.

36:59.292 --> 37:01.434
I NEED YOU
TO GET THIS TOGETHER.

37:01.434 --> 37:03.236
WE'RE GOING DOWN
TO THAT POLICE STATION.

37:03.236 --> 37:05.404
I NEED YOU TO TELL THEM
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW.

37:05.404 --> 37:08.341
[ Crying ] DO WE HAVE ‐‐
DO WE HAVE TO DO THIS NOW?

37:08.341 --> 37:09.408
YES, CHILD.

37:09.408 --> 37:11.911
WHILE IT'S STILL FRESH
IN YOUR MIND.

37:11.911 --> 37:14.180
[ SNIFFLES ]

37:14.180 --> 37:15.749
OKAY.

37:15.749 --> 37:17.483
I'M SO SORRY.

37:17.483 --> 37:19.319
[ SNIFFLES ]

37:19.319 --> 37:23.590
I HOPE YOUR SON
PULLS THROUGH.

37:23.590 --> 37:25.091
THANK YOU.

37:33.299 --> 37:37.070
[ KATHERYN CRYING ]

37:40.273 --> 37:42.509
WOW.

37:42.509 --> 37:43.977
IT DOES CRY.

37:43.977 --> 37:46.446
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

37:46.446 --> 37:50.150
WE HAVE ONE RULE, KATHERYN,
ONE VERY SIMPLE RULE.

37:50.150 --> 37:52.853
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
ABOUT OUR RULES.

37:52.853 --> 37:54.588
JUST ‐‐ JUST
GET OUT OF HERE.

37:54.588 --> 37:57.323
OBVIOUSLY, WHEN THE CHILDREN
ARE PRESENT,

37:57.323 --> 37:59.893
YOU AND I ARE SUPPOSED TO
AT LEAST PRETEND TO BE UNIFIED.

37:59.893 --> 38:00.901
REMEMBER?

38:00.901 --> 38:03.269
WELL, NOT TONIGHT.
FINE BY ME.

38:03.269 --> 38:06.840
THE FURTHER AWAY I GET FROM YOU,
THE BETTER IT IS.

38:06.840 --> 38:08.809
THE FEELING
IS MUTUAL.

38:08.809 --> 38:10.811
WHERE'S WYATT?
IS HE STILL ASLEEP?

38:10.811 --> 38:13.680
WHY?
WHY?

38:13.680 --> 38:15.882
BECAUSE I'D LIKE TO TALK TO HIM.
THAT'S WHY.

38:15.882 --> 38:17.851
YOU MEAN THROW HIM AROUND?
OH, PLEASE.

38:17.851 --> 38:20.386
YOU HAVE ABSOLUTE‐‐
GO AHEAD.

38:20.386 --> 38:22.088
JUST PRETEND
THAT IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

38:22.088 --> 38:24.324
I'M THE REASON WHY THE CHILDREN
TURNED OUT SO BAD.

38:24.324 --> 38:26.026
GOD FORBID
YOU SHOULD EVER TAKE

38:26.026 --> 38:28.161
ANY PERSONAL RESPONSIBILITY
FOR ANYTHING.

38:28.161 --> 38:30.931
I WANT AMANDA AWAY
FROM YOUR WHORE.

38:30.931 --> 38:32.065
DO YOU HEAR ME?

38:32.065 --> 38:34.500
YES, OF COURSE I HEAR YOU
ALL DAY AND ALL NIGHT.

38:34.500 --> 38:36.670
HOW CAN I HELP BUT HEAR YOU,
KATHERYN?

38:36.670 --> 38:38.939
ALL YOUR QUESTIONS
AND YOUR ACCUSATIONS,

38:38.939 --> 38:40.541
THEY SOUND LIKE
THE SAME THING TO ME.

38:40.541 --> 38:41.875
NAG, NAG, NAG.

38:41.875 --> 38:44.344
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?
WHAT?

38:44.344 --> 38:47.514
YOU USED TO BE
SUCH A SON OF A BITCH.

38:47.514 --> 38:49.816
YOU WOULD HAVE EATEN
THAT LITTLE GIRL ALIVE.

38:49.816 --> 38:51.752
I WOULDN'T HAVE HAD TO SAY
A THING.

38:51.752 --> 38:53.053
YOU HAVE ANNIHILATED HER.

38:53.053 --> 38:55.956
WHY SHOULD I BOTHER
SINCE YOU WEAR MY PANTS SO WELL?

38:55.956 --> 38:58.258
WELL, SOMEBODY HAS TO
THESE DAYS.

39:00.226 --> 39:03.136
SHE REALLY DID A NUMBER ON YOU,
DID SHE?

39:03.136 --> 39:04.638
REALLY DID A NUMBER.

39:04.638 --> 39:06.973
WHAT'D SHE MAKE YOU
THINK?

39:06.973 --> 39:09.810
THAT YOU WERE STILL YOUNG
AND STILL SEXY?

39:09.810 --> 39:11.745
HA!

39:11.745 --> 39:13.379
HAVE YOU LOOKED IN THE MIRROR
LATELY, DARLING?

39:13.379 --> 39:15.448
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:15.448 --> 39:18.919
DID YOU REALLY JUST ASK ME
THAT QUESTION? HMM?

39:18.919 --> 39:20.654
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HER.

39:20.654 --> 39:24.991
DAMN IT.
YOU FOUND ME OUT.

39:24.991 --> 39:28.428
YES, KATHERYN CRYER,
I LOVE CANDACE.

39:28.428 --> 39:30.263
DOES THAT HURT YOU?

39:30.263 --> 39:32.899
I WOULDN'T GIVE YOU
THE SATISFACTION

39:32.899 --> 39:34.500
OF KNOWING WHAT HURTS ME.

39:34.500 --> 39:35.736
BELIEVE ME, SWEETHEART,

39:35.736 --> 39:38.104
IF I COULD FALL IN LOVE WITH HER
JUST TO HURT YOU,

39:38.104 --> 39:41.642
I'D DO EVERYTHING IN MY POWER
TO DO JUST THAT.

39:41.642 --> 39:46.079
BUT FORTUNATELY FOR YOU,
THAT'S NOT HOW IT WORKS.

39:46.079 --> 39:49.516
I DON'T LOVE HER, KATHERYN.
SORRY.

39:49.516 --> 39:52.252
GOOD FOR YOU.

39:52.252 --> 39:54.420
'CAUSE I WAS BEGINNING
TO THINK

39:54.420 --> 39:56.890
YOU'RE GETTING SOFT
IN YOUR OLD AGE.

39:56.890 --> 39:58.358
IN MORE WAYS THAN ONE.

39:58.358 --> 40:01.201
OH, I'M JUST AS HARD
AS EVER.

40:01.201 --> 40:05.305
YOU DON'T HAVE THE CHANCE
TO SEE IT ANYMORE, THOUGH.

40:05.305 --> 40:08.308
I'VE SEEN YOUR IDEA OF HARD,
DARLING,

40:08.308 --> 40:11.512
AND TRUST ME,
DOES NOTHING FOR ME.

40:11.512 --> 40:13.146
REALLY?

40:13.146 --> 40:15.616
BECAUSE THAT'S NOT WHAT
YOUR EYES ARE SAYING, KATHERYN.

40:15.616 --> 40:17.417
THAT'S NOT WHAT YOUR MOUTH
IS SAYING.

40:17.417 --> 40:22.756
WHAT YOUR MOUTH IS SAYING IS
THAT YOU WANT ME NOW, BAD.

40:22.756 --> 40:24.290
RIGHT NOW.

40:24.290 --> 40:26.326
RIGHT HERE.

40:26.326 --> 40:27.894
BUT SINCE
I'M NOT INTERESTED,

40:27.894 --> 40:30.130
YOU FEEL THAT YOU HAVE TO
PRETEND TO HATE ME.

40:30.130 --> 40:32.533
HOW'S THAT?

40:32.533 --> 40:35.936
THIS ISN'T PRETENDING,
DARLING.

40:35.936 --> 40:37.704
OH.

40:37.704 --> 40:39.339
RIGHT.

40:39.339 --> 40:41.808
GO TO HELL.
SHOW ME THE WAY.

40:41.808 --> 40:43.376
NEED I REMIND YOU
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN

40:43.376 --> 40:44.945
IF NINE GETS AHOLD
OF AMANDA'S MONEY?

40:44.945 --> 40:48.014
SHE WON'T.
OR IF THIS GOES PUBLIC?

40:48.014 --> 40:49.315
I'LL HANDLE IT.

40:49.315 --> 40:51.552
FOR GOOD, JIM.

40:51.552 --> 40:54.688
YOU WILL HANDLE THIS
FOR GOOD.

40:54.688 --> 40:56.923
DID YOU HEAR ME?
YES!

40:56.923 --> 40:59.359
YES, I HEARD YOU.

40:59.359 --> 41:01.501
AND I WANT AMANDA BACK
IN THIS HOUSE.

41:01.501 --> 41:03.870
IT'D BE A HELL OF A LOT EASIER
IF YOU HADN'T CHASED HER OFF.

41:03.870 --> 41:06.139
GET THE HELL
OUT OF MY ROOM.

41:06.139 --> 41:07.307
[ SCOFFS ]

41:07.307 --> 41:09.175
AND DON'T LET THE DOOR HIT YOU
ON THE WAY OUT.

41:09.175 --> 41:10.844
NICE ONE.
[ TURNS ON T. V. ]

41:10.844 --> 41:13.747
Reporter:
<i>IN A SEPARATE INCIDENT,</i>
<i>POLICE ARE SEEKING INFORMATION</i>

41:13.747 --> 41:15.849
<i>IN A HIT‐AND‐RUN</i>
<i>THAT LEFT A LITTLE GIRL DEAD</i>

41:15.849 --> 41:18.985
<i>AND A MAN INJURED</i>
<i>IN THE 1700 BLOCK OF MATTHEWS.</i>

41:18.985 --> 41:21.922
<i>WITNESSES SAY THE DRIVER WAS</i>
<i>DRIVING A BLACK SEDAN</i>

41:21.922 --> 41:24.324
<i>THAT RAN OVER THE YOUNG GIRL</i>
<i>AND HIT THE MAN</i>

41:24.324 --> 41:26.059
<i>WITHOUT SLOWING DOWN.</i>

41:26.059 --> 41:28.094
<i>POLICE ARE INVESTIGATING.</i>

41:31.832 --> 41:34.568
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:34.568 --> 41:38.004
A LITTLE GIRL IS DEAD.
OH, NO.

41:38.004 --> 41:39.405
HEY, JEFFREY.
YEAH?

41:39.405 --> 41:40.406
I'M SUING MY PARENTS.

41:40.406 --> 41:41.441
WHY IS SHE SUING
HER PARENTS?

41:41.441 --> 41:42.676
SHE TOLD YOU THAT?

41:42.676 --> 41:43.977
IS HANNA HERE?
DID SHE SHOW UP FOR WORK YET?

41:43.977 --> 41:45.546
SHE WON'T SAY ANYTHING, JIM.

41:45.546 --> 41:47.247
MISS YOUNG,
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU.

41:47.247 --> 41:48.649
YOU'RE GONNA JOIN US.

41:48.649 --> 41:50.551
AMANDA, WHAT THE HELL ARE
YOU DOING IN MY NEIGHBORHOOD?

41:50.551 --> 41:52.152
STATE'S ABOUT TO BE IN THE
MIDDLE OF A NATIONAL SPOTLIGHT

41:52.152 --> 41:54.521
IF WE CAN'T WRAP OUR
ARMS AROUND THAT LITTLE
GIRL WHO WAS KILLED.

41:54.521 --> 41:56.356
POLICE HAVE ANY SUSPECTS,
ANY LEADS, ANYTHING AT ALL?

41:56.356 --> 41:58.324
HAVE YOU SEEN THIS?
AM I GOING TO JAIL?

41:58.324 --> 41:59.826
THE BLACK SEDAN
IS YOUR SON'S CAR.

41:59.826 --> 42:01.101
WHAT?
